---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Codex Guide" description="Configure Codex CLI as the preferred BridgeAIChat beta tool.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Tool Guide</div>
    <h1>Codex is the cleanest beta path today.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      BridgeAIChat currently treats Codex as the primary happy path because it gives predictable one-shot execution
      and cleaner local setup than quota-bound or auth-fragile alternatives.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Recommended</div>
      <h2>Typical config shape</h2>
      <pre>tools:
  codex:
    cmd: codex
    args: ["exec", "--skip-git-repo-check", "--full-auto"]
    working_dir: ..</pre>
      <p>Set <code>working_dir</code> to the project root you want the CLI to operate inside. The beta uses one-shot execution rather than a long-lived interactive Codex session.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Notes</div>
      <h2>What to expect</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Codex replies are trimmed to the final assistant message instead of raw terminal transcript</li>
        <li>Per-chat Codex session resume is not yet the default beta path</li>
        <li>The agent device must have the <code>codex</code> binary installed and available to the configured command path</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
